==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Swirl
<hw>Swirl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Swirled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Swirling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Akin to Norw.
<ets>svirla</ets> to whirl, freq. of <ets>sverra</ets> to whirl, Dan.
<ets>svirre</ets>, G. <ets>schwirren</ets> to whiz, to buzz. ⟦root⟧177.
See <er>Swarm</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>To whirl, or cause to
whirl, as in an eddy.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The river <xex>swirled</xex>
along.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>C. Kingsley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swirl</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Swirl
<hw>Swirl</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A whirling motion; an eddy, as of
water; a whirl.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The silent <xex>swirl</xex> of bats.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Mrs. Browning.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

